AB  - In the orthodox models of trade, terms of trade loss (in the absence of growth) implies national immiserisation. The present paper demonstrates, however, that when trade is restricted by a fixed and binding quota and the premia associated with imports are dissipated via rent-seeking activities, a decline in the terms of trade, by paradoxically reducing the social cost of imports, may improve national welfare.
ER  - 
